data.description: Country living at the base of the Cascades. This charming 3 br /2 bath 1940's bungalow sits on a large .27 acre lot nestled on a quiet lane in the small but vibrant town of Wamic. Sportsman's paradise with quick access to the Deschutes River, Pine Hollow Reservoir, Mt Hood Natl Forest, Wilderness, and just 45 minutes to Mt Hood and the Hood River. On the main level, you'll find a spacious living room with rock fireplace, large kitchen, two bedrooms and large enclosed patio room. Downstairs, you'll find a large family room, bedroom, laundry & utility room, 2nd bathroom, and hot tub to help sooth your muscles after a day of hiking or gardening. Warm summer days will beckon you to lounge on the large back deck and cool off in the above ground pool while you enjoy the view of the surrounding country side. Detached 1-car garage, storage area, and large driveway has plenty of room to store your things including boats, RV, and anything else you'll want to enjoy this beautiful part of Oregon!
